== Beef Filling ==

Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Heat a medium #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. > IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the beef cooks, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Add the garlic, @Central American style spice mix{2%tsp} and @tomato puree{30%g} to the browned beef, then stir-fry for ~{1%min}.

Stir in the @water{75%ml} for the sauce and cook until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once thickened, remove from the heat and stir in the @BBQ sauce{32%g}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

== Quesadillas ==

Lay the @plain taco tortillas{4} (2 per person) onto a lightly oiled #baking tray{} and spoon the beef filling onto one half of each one.

Top with the cheese, then fold the other side over to make a semi-circle. Press down to keep together.

Rub a little @oil{} over the top of each one.

Bake your quesadillas on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{5-7%minutes}.

== Baby Gem and Tomato Salad ==

While the quesadillas bake, pop the @cider vinegar{15%ml} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing into a large #bowl{}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix together.

Cut the @medium tomato{1} into 1cm pieces and add them to the dressing.

Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice widthways.

Just before serving, add the baby gem to the bowl of dressing and toss to coat.

== To Serve ==

When ready, share the BBQ beef quesadillas between your plates.

Serve with the salad alongside. Enjoy!

> Cider vinegar and olive oil amounts are approximate - adjust to taste.